SAMPLE RUN:
This program will calculate the total cost to drive 20, 75, and 500 miles using the mpg for a vehicle and price/gallon of fuel.

Enter the mpg rating for your car: 
(user inputs value)
Ex. 25

Enter the price per gallon for gas: 
(user inputs value)
Ex. 3.00

It will cost:
2.40 dollars to travel 20 miles
9.00 dollars to travel 75 miles
60 dollars to travel 500 miles


===========================================================
DESIGN:

a) Inputs
double milesPerGallon
double pricePerGallon

-----------------------------------------------------------
b) Outputs
double costFor20Miles, double costFor75Miles, double costFor500Miles

-----------------------------------------------------------
c) Calculations

costFor20miles = (20 / milesPerGallon) * (pricePerGallon)
costFor75Miles = (75 / milesPerGallon) * (pricePerGallon)
costFor500Miles = (500 / milesPerGallon) * (pricePerGallon)
-----------------------------------------------------------
d) Pseudocode
DECLARE double milesPerGallon
DECLARE double pricePerGallon

DECLARE double costFor20Miles
DECLARE double costFor75Miles
DECLARE double costFor500Miles

DISPLAY "This program will calculate the total cost to drive 20 miles, 75 miles, and 500 miles"

DISPLAY "Enter the mpg rating for your car: "
INPUT milesPerGallon

DISPLAY "Enter the price per gallon for gas: "
INPUT pricePerGallon

SET costFor20Miles = (20 / milesPerGallon) * (pricePerGallon)
SET costFor75Miles = (75 / milesPerGallon) * (pricePerGallon)
SET costFor500Miles = (500 / milesPerGallon) * (pricePerGallon)

DISPLAY "It will cost " costFor20Miles " dollars to travel 20 miles, " costFor75Miles " dollars to travel 75 Miles, and " costFor500Miles " dollars to travel 500 miles."